de.tudarmstadt.ukp.lmf.model.morphology
Class WordForm

java.lang.Object
  de.tudarmstadt.ukp.lmf.model.abstracts.HasFrequencies
      de.tudarmstadt.ukp.lmf.model.morphology.WordForm
All Implemented Interfaces:
IHasFrequencies
public class WordForm
extends HasFrequencies

WordForm is a class representing a form that a lexeme, represented by a LexicalEntry instance, can take when used in a sentence or a phrase. WordForm class contains at least one FormRepresentation instance.

Author:
Zijad Maksuti

getFormRepresentations

public java.util.List<FormRepresentation> getFormRepresentations()
Returns the List of all FormRepresentation instances of this WordForm.

Returns:
the list of all form representations of this word form or an empty list, if the word form does not have any form representations set.

Note that, according to Uby-LMF, every word form contains at least one form representation. Absence of form representations in a word form may indicate an error in the conversion of the original resource.
